The following `search` method is full of callbacks:

```typescript
search(onResult: (match: ISerializedFileMatch[]) => void, onProgress: (progress: IProgress) => void, done: (error: Error, complete: ISerializedSearchComplete) => void): void
```

We've long ago decided to drop callbacks in favour of promises, which are easier to reason about, compose and maintain.

My suggestion is to combine `onResult` with `onProgress`, they are one and the same.

```typescript
interface ISearchProgress {
  results: ISerializedFileMatch[];
  progress: IProgress;
}

search(): PPromise<ISerializedSearchComplete, ISearchProgress>;
```
